    "Furthermore, GPT-2 lacks a fine-tuning stage for downstream tasks, which, despite its extensive pre-training on large corpora enabling decent performance in various NLP tasks, results in comparatively inferior performance to models incorporating a supervised learning fine-tuning stage.As the BERT model stands as the second-best performer, we proceed to a comparison between the ALBERT model and BERT."
